cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.CE 

The paper proposes a methodology to automate the result evaluation step in an analytic process using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). This involves learning an analyst's intent to identify interesting plots in production yield data analytics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as GANs are a popular deep learning technique. The paper also involves aspects of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it proposes a methodology for automating a step in an analytic process. Additionally, the paper deals with data analysis and optimization, which falls under the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
